{"meta":{"updateDate":1755117017720,"pPcc":"SAT#S","questionId":"0e40dfb0","skill_cd":"S.A.","score_band_range_cd":3,"skill_desc":"Area and volume","createDate":1755117017720,"program":"SAT","primary_class_cd_desc":"Geometry and Trigonometry","ibn":"","external_id":"7fb7e2c6-237c-42b9-a178-4810e8c6cd93","primary_class_cd":"S","uId":"521eca69-8d4c-4c53-a075-c01e4ebc3d03","difficulty":"E"},"source":"modern","detail":{"type":"mcq","stem":"<p style=\"text-align: left;\">A rectangle has a length of <math alttext=\"3\"><mn>3</mn>\n</math> units and a width of <math alttext=\"39\"><mn>39</mn>\n</math> units. Which expression gives the area, in square units, of this rectangle?</p>","keys":["f882fb3c-ad86-4011-8776-03edc558cfa5"],"answerOptions":[{"id":"386bf8f1-3e5d-4df5-ba40-c25960b15d09","content":"<p><math alttext=\"2 left parenthesis 3 plus 39 right parenthesis\"><mn>2</mn><mfenced><mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow><mo>+</mo><mrow><mn>39</mn></mrow></mrow></mfenced></math></p>"},{"id":"3edcaf54-94e8-4b26-84e0-bcd7bb5a80e2","content":"<p><math alttext=\"2 left parenthesis 3 dot 39 right parenthesis\"><mn>2</mn><mfenced><mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow><mo>&#183;</mo><mrow><mn>39</mn></mrow></mrow></mfenced></math></p>"},{"id":"6ab3b006-ddf3-4f75-9679-141fe97565db","content":"<p><math alttext=\"3 plus 39\"><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow><mo>+</mo><mrow><mn>39</mn></mrow></math></p>"},{"id":"f882fb3c-ad86-4011-8776-03edc558cfa5","content":"<p><math alttext=\"3 dot 39\"><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow><mo>&#183;</mo><mrow><mn>39</mn></mrow></math></p>"}],"rationale":"<p>Choice D is correct. The area of a rectangle is given by&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"script l w\"><mi mathvariant=\"script\">l</mi><mi>w</mi></math>, where&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"script l\"><mi mathvariant=\"script\">l</mi></math> is the length of the rectangle and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"w\"><mi>w</mi></math> is the width of the rectangle. It's given that a rectangle has a length of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"3\"><mn>3</mn></math> units and a width of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"39\"><mn>39</mn></math> units. It follows that the area of the rectangle is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"3 dot 39\"><mn>3</mn><mo>&#183;</mo><mn>39</mn></math> square units. Therefore, the expression that gives the area, in square units, of this rectangle, is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"3 dot 39\"><mn>3</mn><mo>&#183;</mo><mn>39</mn></math>.</p>\n<p>Choice A is incorrect. This expression gives the perimeter, in units, of this rectangle.</p>\n<p>Choice B is incorrect and may result from conceptual errors.</p>\n<p>Choice C is incorrect and may result from conceptual errors.</p>","externalid":"7fb7e2c6-237c-42b9-a178-4810e8c6cd93","correct_answer":["D"]}}